<TITLE>Ofélia Ramos Anunciato</TITLE>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="1" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="plain_name" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name" NEW="yes">Ofélia Ramos Anunciato</REFEX>
</REF>
 or Ofélia (1924 – 1998) was a well-known Brazilian chef. 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="2" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">she</REFEX>
</REF>
 hosted cooking shows on TV, like A cozinha Maravilhosa de Ofélia. 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="3" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">she</REFEX>
</REF>
 began 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="4" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj-det" PREDICTION="genitive_pronoun_him" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="genitive" TAG="genitive_pronoun_him" NEW="yes">her</REFEX>
</REF>
 career as a personality chef by publishing recipes in 1958 in the newspapers A Tribuna (Santos, São Paulo) and A Gazeta (also in São Paulo). Ofélia, A Taste of Brazil is a translation from Portuguese by 
<REF ENTITY="1" MENTION="1" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="obj" PREDICTION="plain_name" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="1" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name" NEW="yes">Julie Martin</REFEX>
</REF>
 (Melhoramentos/2000).
